cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action recognition in videos using convolutional neural networks. The use of Residual Networks (ResNets) also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of spatiotemporal networks suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also involves training the model end-to-end, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep architectures and hierarchical learning suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
